Paul L. FriedmanPrincipal, Friedman & Associates L.L.C.LocationGreater St. Louis AreaIndustryManagement ConsultingCurrentFriedman & Associates L.L.C.EducationSaint Louis University11 connectionsView Paul L.’s full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View Paul L.’s Full ProfileSummaryMr. Paul L. Friedman is the founding principal of Friedman & Associates, a consulting firm with special emphasis on facility-related issues.  With more than 35 years of management experience as a Principal in the office interiors industry, he has collaborated with major furniture manufacturers, as well as real estate, facility and purchasing professionals, in the development of strategies and pricing structures that ultimately led to successful contract negotiations with numerous Fortune 500 corporations.  In his role as a consultant to major corporations and large employers, Mr. Friedman has assisted in sophisticated facility projects with his special expertise in areas of facility selection, cost containment, value enhancement, product and vendor analysis, logistics and move management, as well as resolution of challenging facility and product related problemsMr. Friedman’s educational resume includes degrees in business, finance and management sciences, completing both graduate and post graduate work.  He has studied, and observed first-hand, the nuances of negotiation from both the vendor’s and the facility professional’s points of view.   He has lectured at Washington University in St. Louis, St. Louis University, and the University of Missouri - St. Louis, and privately to various corporate clients.  He has also served on various boards of not-for profit organizations.Specialties: Facilities management issues with respect to product selection, contract negotiations, move management, problem resolution, surplus furniture disposal and similarly related mattersExperiencePrincipalFriedman & Associates L.L.C.1971  –  Presen